## CPU Profiling (pyinstrument)

[pyinstrument](https://github.com/joerick/pyinstrument) is a statistical CPU
profiler with async support and HTML output.

### Context Manager

```python
from {{ project_slug }}.infrastructure.profiling import cpu_profile

async with cpu_profile(label="my_operation") as result:
    await some_expensive_operation()

print(f"Duration: {result.duration_s:.3f}s")
print(f"Report: {result.html_path}")
```

### Decorator

```python
from {{ project_slug }}.infrastructure.profiling.cpu import profile_function

@profile_function(label="process_batch")
async def process_batch(items: list[Item]) -> list[Result]:
    ...
```

### Task Runner

```bash
task backend:profile:cpu  # Profile app startup with pyinstrument → HTML report
```

