## Middleware (On-Demand Request Profiling)

The `ProfilingMiddleware` enables per-request profiling via query parameters.

| Query Parameter | Effect |
|----------------|--------|
| `?profile=1` or `?profile=cpu` | CPU profiling via pyinstrument |

### Security

Protected by two guards:

1. **`{{ project_slug | upper }}_PROFILING_ENABLED=true`** (default: `false`)
2. **`X-Profile-Secret` header** must match `{{ project_slug | upper }}_PROFILING_SECRET`

```bash
curl -H "X-Profile-Secret: my-secret" \
     "http://localhost:8000/api/v1/users?profile=cpu"
```

### Response Headers

| Header | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `Server-Timing: profile;dur=<ms>` | Profiled request duration |
| `X-Profile-Saved` | Set to `true` when a profile report was saved |

The `TimingMiddleware` adds `Server-Timing: total;dur=<ms>` to every response
and logs the duration via structured logging.

